{
  "texts": [
    "In the next step of the decomposition plan, E3 categorized the products to explore the temporal trends of different categories (Fig. 7-a2).",
    "It was found that the temporal trends of the different categories were broadly similar, but the total sales volume of the technology category in November was the highest.",
    "Moreover, following the agent's decomposition into another task: \"Analyze sales trends of top-selling and bottom-selling products\", E3 noted that in the domain scenario, \"finding out how well products are selling can optimize inventory to prevent stockouts and excess inventory.\"",
    "Therefore, E3 selected a task previously proposed but not executed, recommended for review by the agent, to rank the sales volumes of different categories and subcategories (Fig. 7-a3).",
    "Based on the generated visualization, E3 discovered that the \"phone\" subcategory within the \"Technology\" category has the best sales performance.After finding the answer to the previous task, E3 was interested in \"analyze the correlation between sales and profit.\""
  ]
}